# Configurar la fecha como ndice

data_exxon.set_index('Date', inplace=True)

# Funcin para prueba de estacionariedad (ADF Test)
def adf_test(series, title=''):
    result = adfuller(series.dropna())
    print(f'ADF Test for {title}:')
    print(f'ADF Statistic: {result[0]}')
    print(f'p-value: {result[1]}')
    print('Stationary' if result[1] < 0.05 else 'Non-Stationary')
    print('')

# Aplicar ADF test a cada serie
adf_test(data_walmart['Close'], 'Walmart')
adf_test(data_pfizer['Close'], 'Pfizer')
adf_test(data_exxon['Close'], 'Exxon')
adf_test(data_jpmorgan['Close'], 'JPMorgan')
adf_test(data_apple['Close'], 'Apple')

# Diferenciar las series para hacerlas estacionarias si es necesario
data_walmart_diff = data_walmart['Close'].diff().dropna()
data_pfizer_diff = data_pfizer['Close'].diff().dropna()
data_exxon_diff = data_exxon['Close'].diff().dropna()
data_jpmorgan_diff = data_jpmorgan['Close'].diff().dropna()
data_apple_diff = data_apple['Close'].diff().dropna()

# Volver a probar estacionariedad en las series diferenciadas
adf_test(data_walmart_diff, 'Walmart Differentiated')
adf_test(data_pfizer_diff, 'Pfizer Differentiated')
adf_test(data_exxon_diff, 'Exxon Differentiated')
adf_test(data_jpmorgan_diff, 'JPMorgan Differentiated')
adf_test(data_apple_diff, 'Apple Differentiated')

# Prueba de cointegracin entre pares de activos
def coint_test(series1, series2, name1, name2):
    score, p_value, _ = coint(series1, series2)
    print(f'Cointegration Test between {name1} and {name2}:')
    print(f'p-value: {p_value}')
    print('Cointegrated' if p_value < 0.05 else 'Not Cointegrated')
    print('')

coint_test(data_walmart['Close'], data_pfizer['Close'], 'Walmart', 'Pfizer')
coint_test(data_walmart['Close'], data_exxon['Close'], 'Walmart', 'Exxon')
coint_test(data_walmart['Close'], data_jpmorgan['Close'], 'Walmart', 'JPMorgan')
coint_test(data_walmart['Close'], data_apple['Close'], 'Walmart', 'Apple')

# Ajuste de modelo AR(1) para Walmart como ejemplo
ar_model = AutoReg(data_walmart_diff, lags=1).fit()
print(ar_model.summary())

# Ajuste de modelo ARIMA para Walmart (p=1, d=1, q=1)
arima_model = ARIMA(data_walmart['Close'], order=(1, 1, 1)).fit()
print(arima_model.summary())

# Pronstico con ARIMA para Walmart
forecast_steps = 10
forecast = arima_model.forecast(steps=forecast_steps)
forecast_index = pd.date_range(start=data_walmart.index[-1], periods=forecast_steps + 1, freq='B')[1:]

# Visualizacin del pronstico
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
plt.plot(data_walmart['Close'], label='Walmart Historical')
plt.plot(forecast_index, forecast, label='Walmart Forecast', color='red')
plt.title('Walmart Stock Price Forecast')
plt.legend()
plt.show()

# Estrategia de portafolio simple basada en pronsticos
# Si el pronstico sube, comprar; si baja, vender
last_forecast = forecast.iloc[-1]
last_price = data_walmart['Close'].iloc[-1]
if last_forecast > last_price:
    print("Recomendacin para Walmart: Comprar")
else:
    print("Recomendacin para Walmart: Vender")

# Diferenciar las series para hacerlas estacionarias
diff_assets = {name: series.diff().dropna() for name, series in assets.items()}

# Funcin para prueba de estacionariedad (ADF Test)
def adf_test(series, title=''):
    result = adfuller(series.dropna())
    print(f'ADF Test for {title}:')
    print(f'p-value: {result[1]}')
    print('Stationary' if result[1] < 0.05 else 'Non-Stationary')
    print('')

# Probar estacionariedad en las series originales y diferenciadas
for name, series in assets.items():
    adf_test(series, f'{name} Original')
for name, series in diff_assets.items():
    adf_test(series, f'{name} Differentiated')

# Graficar series originales
plt.figure(figsize=(15, 10))
for i, (name, series) in enumerate(assets.items(), 1):
    plt.subplot(3, 2, i)
    plt.plot(series, label=f'{name} Original')
    plt.title(f'{name} - Original Series')
    plt.legend()
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# Graficar series diferenciadas
plt.figure(figsize=(15, 10))
for i, (name, series) in enumerate(diff_assets.items(), 1):
    plt.subplot(3, 2, i)
    plt.plot(series, label=f'{name} Differentiated', color='orange')
    plt.title(f'{name} - Differentiated Series')
    plt.legend()
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# Comparacin de modelos AR, ARMA y ARIMA
for name, series in assets.items():
    print(f"\n=== Modelos para {name} ===")

    # AR(1)
    ar_model = AutoReg(diff_assets[name], lags=1).fit()
    print(f"AR(1) para {name} - AIC: {ar_model.aic}")

    # ARMA(1,1) - Usamos ARIMA con d=0 para simular ARMA
    arma_model = ARIMA(series, order=(1, 0, 1)).fit()
    print(f"ARMA(1,1) para {name} - AIC: {arma_model.aic}")

    # ARIMA(1,1,1)
    arima_model = ARIMA(series, order=(1, 1, 1)).fit()
    print(f"ARIMA(1,1,1) para {name} - AIC: {arima_model.aic}")
    print("")

forecasts = {}
for name, series in assets.items():
    # Ajustar modelo ARIMA(1,1,1)
    model = ARIMA(series, order=(1, 1, 1)).fit()
    # Pronosticar
    forecast = model.forecast(steps=forecast_steps)
    forecast_index = pd.date_range(start=series.index[-1], periods=forecast_steps + 1, freq='B')[1:]
    forecasts[name] = (forecast, forecast_index)

# Graficar los pronsticos
plt.figure(figsize=(15, 10))
for i, (name, (forecast, forecast_index)) in enumerate(forecasts.items(), 1):
    plt.subplot(3, 2, i)
    plt.plot(assets[name], label=f'{name} Historical')
    plt.plot(forecast_index, forecast, label=f'{name} Forecast', color='red')
    plt.title(f'{name} Stock Price Forecast')
    plt.legend()
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# Recomendaciones basadas en el pronstico
for name, (forecast, _) in forecasts.items():
    last_forecast = forecast.iloc[-1]
    last_price = assets[name].iloc[-1]
    print(f"\nRecomendacin para {name}:")
    if last_forecast > last_price:
        print("Comprar")
    else:
        print("Vender")

#@title Convert ipynb to HTML in Colab
# Upload ipynb
from google.colab import files
f = files.upload()

# Convert ipynb to html
import subprocess
file0 = list(f.keys())[0]
_ = subprocess.run(["pip", "install", "nbconvert"])
_ = subprocess.run(["jupyter", "nbconvert", file0, "--to", "html"])

# download the html
files.download(file0[:-5]+"html")
